This type of cultural combination is associated with success in business and industrial production, and organizations that score high in these dimensions could benefit from implementing strategies involved in industrial organization theory. For example, to enhance a company's competitiveness, organizations could focus on strategies to improve its products and/or services, invest in human capital and technology, and speed up the processes for organizing and managing information. Finally, case studies can be used to explore applications in various fields.
